ssages_conversation_id` index for the WHERE clause and then sort, but a composit
e index would be more efficient for `WHERE conversation_id = ? ORDER BY sequence
_id DESC`.\n\n### 3. Snowflake concurrency concern\n`Snowflake.nextId()` is not 
thread-safe for multi-process scenarios (PM2 cluster mode). Multiple API instanc
es could generate the same sequence_id. This is noted indirectly in the tech-deb
t-tracker but the Snowflake implementation doesn\'t include a worker ID.\n\n### 
