mit `message:receive`."\n\nThis is NOT implemented in the current code. The `_on
ImConnectRequested` in the BLoC just connects to socket but doesn\'t emit any `m
essage:sync`. And the gateway doesn\'t have a handler for `message:sync`.\n\nThi
s is a significant gap - when a user reconnects after being offline, they won\'t
receive missed messages.\n\n### 6. Push notification service not implemented\nTh
e BDD test explicitly notes: "Push notification service is not yet implemented" 
and this is tracked in tech-debt-tracker. This is acceptable for MVP per the PRD
.\n\n### 7. `sw_chat_bubble.dart` uses `Theme.of(context).colorScheme.surface` a
nd `MediaQuery.of(context).size.width * 0.7`\n- Uses `Theme.of(context).colorSch
eme.surface` which is correct per flutter.md\n- BUT `MediaQuery.of(context).size
.width * 0.7` is a hardcoded ratio. The Flutter spec says "不使用硬编码颜色/字号
". While width ratio is not exactly a color/size, it could be considered a desig
n token.\n\n### 8. `_buildChatItems` doesn\'t de-duplicate messages\nIn `chat_pa
ge.dart`, the `_buildChatItems` method builds display items from the `messages` 
list. But it doesn\'t handle de-duplication by `client_message_id`. Messages wit
h the same `client_message_id` could appear twice (temp message and server-confi
rmed message). Though the BLoC does try to update the temp message on ack, there
could be edge cases.\n\n### 9. The `getConversations` cursor is `updated_at` bas
ed, which might miss changes\nThe cursor pagination uses `c.updated_at < :cursor
`. But if multiple conversations have the exact same `updated_at`, the paginatio
n might skip or duplicate entries. Using a combination like `(updated_at, id)` w
ould be safer.\n\n### 10. Native SQL uses `?` (correct per template checklist)\n
\n### 11. Entity registration in module - VERIFIED\nThe `im.module.ts` registers
all entities in `TypeOrmModule.forFeature([MessageEntity, ConversationEntity, Co
nversationParticipantEntity, UserProfileEntity])`. \n\n### 12. Entity already ha
s `autoLoadEntities: true` in app.module.ts - but this is for auto-discovery. Ma
nual registration is also correct.\n\n### 13. Socket.io events are emitted after
transaction commit - VERIFIED\nThe `sendMessage` completes the transaction insid
e the service, then the gateway emits events after receiving the response. ✅\n\
n### 14. Pusher notification not implemented but tracked in tech debt\n\n### 15.
