ges` 表中 `sequence_id > last_ack_sequence_id` 的记录，批量 emit `message:receiv
e`." This is completely absent — no handler in gateway, no emit from client. Wit
hout this, reconnecting users will permanently miss messages sent while they wer
e offline. The REST API `GET /messages` can partially compensate, but the spec e
xplicitly calls for socket-based catch-up.\n\n2. **Missing composite index `(con
versation_id, sequence_id)` on messages table**: The execution plan explicitly s
tates "必须建立索引 `(conversation_id, sequence_id)`". The migration creates sep
arate indexes `idx_messages_conversation_id` and `idx_messages_sequence_id` but 
no composite index. The pagination query `WHERE m.conversation_id = ? ORDER BY m
.sequence_id DESC` will work sub-optimally. While MySQL can use index merge, a d
edicated composite index is more predictable and performant.\n\n## Major Issues:
\n\n3. **No front-end handler for `message:error` event**: The gateway emits `me
ssage:error` on various failure scenarios (send failures, auth failures, read fa
ilures), but the `im_socket_client.dart` has no handler for this event. Error fe
edback to the user is lost.\n\n4. **`Snowflake.nextId()` lacks worker/node ID**:
